# Binary

A binary file is any file that cannot be interpreted as a text file.
From a structural standpoint, a binary file can be seen as sequence of bytes.


## Extensions

SPARQL Anything selects this transformer for the following file extensions:

- bin
- bmp
- dat
- ico
- jpeg
- jpg
- png
- tif
- tiff

## Media types

SPARQL Anything selects this transformer for the following media types:

- application/octet-stream
- image/bmp
- image/jpeg
- image/png
- image/tiff
- image/vnd.microsoft.icon

## Default implementation

- [io.github.sparqlanything.binary.BinaryTriplifier](../sparql-anything-binary/src/main/java/io/github/sparqlanything/binary/BinaryTriplifier.java)
